{"id":"nethaniah","term":"Nethaniah","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Given of Jehovah. (1.) One of Asaph’s sons, appointed by David to minister in the temple (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 25:2\">1 Chr. 25:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 25:12\">12</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) A Levite sent by Jehoshaphat to teach the law (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 17:8\">2 Chr. 17:8</a>).</p>\n<p>(3.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 36:14\">Jer. 36:14</a>.</p>\n<p>(4.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 25:23\">2 Kings 25:23</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 25:25\">25</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 25:2","1 Chronicles 25:12","2 Chronicles 17:8","Jeremiah 36:14","2 Kings 25:23","2 Kings 25:25"]}